&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Salesforce Developer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Who We Are&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Orion Global Solutions, we’re not your typical tech consultancy. As a Salesforce Summit Partner (the highest tier!) and one of the fastest-growing Salesforce partners in the New York Metro area, we bring innovation, speed, and genuine collaboration to every client interaction. But what truly sets us apart?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a fast-growing, people-first U.S. company that believes in building thoughtful, user-friendly systems to support our employees and customers. As we expand, we’re looking for talented&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Sr. Salesforce Developers&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in Canada, who bring both technical know-how and strong collaboration skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to a&amp;nbsp;remote-first culture&amp;nbsp;that enables you to thrive in your role—no need to relocate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Salesforce Developer&lt;/strong&gt;, you’ll help design, build, and maintain Salesforce solutions that support our internal teams and business growth. You&#39;ll collaborate with cross-functional teams, contribute to scalable architecture, and be part of a company where your impact is visible and valued.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What&amp;nbsp;You’ll&amp;nbsp;Be Doing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customize and configure Salesforce using Apex, Lightning Web Components, and declarative tools.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business needs into technical solutions within Sales Cloud and Service Cloud.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate Salesforce with third-party tools and internal systems (APIs, middleware, etc.).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clean, scalable code and contribute to peer reviews and architecture discussions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in Agile sprints, support QA/UAT testing, and help drive technical best practices.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You Bring&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of Salesforce development experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in Apex, SOQL, and Lightning Web Components (LWC)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with declarative tools like Flow, Process Builder, and Validation Rules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with integrations (REST/SOAP APIs, middleware like MuleSoft or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of Salesforce security, deployment, and version control tools (Gearset, Copado, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salesforce certifications (Platform Developer I/II, Admin, App Builder, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience working with U.S. teams or companies&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good written and spoken English (B2+ level or higher)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable home office setup with a stable internet connection&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eligible to work in the U.S.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required to have a Canadian passport or a valid US visitor visa to enter the US and attend meetings.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
